  "prompt": "How did the ring come to Sauron?",
  "response": "In J.R.R. Tolkien's legendarium, the One Ring was created by Sauron himself during the Second Age of Middle-earth. Sauron disguised himself as Annatar, the \"Lord of Gifts,\" and deceived the Elves of Eregion, led by Celebrimbor, into forging the Rings of Power. He then secretly forged the One Ring in the fires of Mount Doom, investing a significant portion of his own power into it. The purpose of the One Ring was to rule over the other Rings of Power and their bearers, thus giving Sauron dominion over Middle-earth.\n\nThe Ring inherently belonged to Sauron, as it was his creation designed to augment his power and control. When he wore the One Ring, he commanded great power, but when it was cut from his finger by Isildur during the battle at the end of the Second Age, Sauron lost his physical form and much of his strength, although his spirit endured. The One Ring eventually came into the possession of Gollum, and then later Bilbo Baggins and Frodo Baggins, but its ultimate destiny was forever tied to Sauron as its master.",
